.SH NAME
\fB²DPROG² \- Gelbe Liste import\fR: imports the monthly "Gelbe Liste" medication reference database from Firebird into MariaDB
.br
(manpage-Hilfe in deutsch verfügbar: 'man ²DPROG²' oder 'man -Lde ²DPROG²')
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB²DPROG² [-<shortopt>|--<longopt> [<supplement>]] ...\fR
.SH SHORT DESCRIPTION
\fB²DPROG²\fR is a command line program that looks in the source directory \fB/DATA/down/neu/GL\fR for new, monthly published data sets of the German medication reference database \fIGelbe Liste\fR (a Firebird database shipped as \fBdatenbank.zip\fR).
.br
The most recent data set is unpacked, read via \fBFirebird\fR (command line tool \fBisql-fb\fR), and the table \fBGL_PCK\fR (packages with PZN, active ingredient, trade name etc.) is imported into the MariaDB table \fBglalle\fR. Afterwards a Firebird backup of the database is archived with \fBgbak\fR.
.br
The program is suited for the regular update of the medication reference data used in the practice management system (among others for mapping PZN to active ingredient/trade name, see also \fBpznbdt\fR).
.SH INSTALLATION
.br
First, please read the chapters 'Functionality', 'Preconditions', 'Automatically installed software packages' and 'Implications' below. Then, if connected to the internet, call (e.g. by copying the line and pasting it into a terminal):
.br
\fBN=²DPROG²;P=${N}_inst.sh;cd ~;wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/²gitv²/$N/master/install.sh -O$P&&sh $P\fR
.br
At last, call:
.br
 \fB²DPROG²\fR
.br
and answer some questions of the program.
.SH USAGE
Ideally, the program should have installed itself after the first call(s) and one-time answering of some questions in a self-running way.
.br
The program is typically called periodically via \fBcron\fR (option \fB-cm\fR/\fB--cronminutes\fR) and then autonomously checks whether a new, not yet imported data set is present in the source directory.
.br
Already imported monthly data sets are recognised (and skipped) by the presence of a Firebird backup file (\fB.fbk\fR) in the source directory.
