.SH FUNCTIONALITY
.LP
When called, '\fB²DPROG²\fR' accomplishes the following:
.LP
\fB1)\fR General and program-specific defaults are set.
.LP
\fB2)\fR Defaults are loaded from the configuration file, if it exists (default: \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the same directory as \fB²DPROG²\fR, default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/²DPROG²\fR).
.LP
\fB3)\fR Command line arguments are evaluated and override the configuration file where applicable.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Questions are asked if values are missing or an interactive option is set.
.LP
\fB5)\fR The program inserts itself if wanted and necessary into root's \fBcrontab\fR in order to be called in adjustable intervals.
.LP
\fB6)\fR The MariaDB database is initialised.
.LP
\fB7)\fR The source directory \fB/DATA/down/neu/GL\fR is searched for subdirectories containing a file \fBdatenbank.zip\fR (name pattern includes \fBGL_YYYY_MM\fR), sorted by modification date.
.LP
\fB8)\fR For each data set not yet archived (identified by the absence of the corresponding \fB.fbk\fR backup file in the source directory), \fBdatenbank.zip\fR is unpacked with \fB7z\fR; the contained Firebird database file \fBgelbeliste.fdb\fR is copied to \fB/opt/firebird/gl\fR.
.LP
\fB9)\fR Via \fBisql-fb\fR, the structure of the Firebird table \fBGL_PCK\fR is read, translated into a corresponding MariaDB table structure, and the data is exported column-wise as text files.
.LP
\fB10)\fR The exported data is loaded into the MariaDB table \fBglalle\fR (database \fBquelle\fR); if the table is missing or its columns differ, it is created or amended.
.LP
\fB11)\fR A backup file (\fB.fbk\fR) of the copied Firebird database is created in the source directory with \fBgbak\fR; its presence marks the data set as already imported on the next call.
.LP
\fB12)\fR The configuration file is written if necessary.
.LP
\fB13)\fR If the option \fB-autoupd\fR is active, the program's version number is compared with that of the installation source and, if behind, an update is performed.
.SH PRECONDITIONS
\fBHardware\fR: Access to the source directory containing the monthly Gelbe Liste data sets (typically a directory populated by download).
.br
\fBSoftware\fR: The program is adjusted to an installation of Opensuse >= 42.1, Debian >= 9, Ubuntu >= 16.04, Mint >= 18 or Fedora >= 24 with standard options. System D must be installed. One of the packet managers \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR or \fBzypper\fR must be installed. The program '\fBwget\fR' must be installed. MariaDB must be running. \fBFirebird SuperServer\fR (32-bit, see installation notes in the source code) with the command line tools \fBisql-fb\fR and \fBgbak\fR under \fB/opt/firebird/bin/\fR is required. \fB7z\fR (p7zip) is required for unpacking.
.SH AUTOMATICALLY INSTALLED SOFTWARE PACKAGES
.br
(for this purpose, depending on the distribution, zypper, apt(-get), dnf or yum are used).
.LP
\fI\fBMakefile:\fR
.br
gcc V.6 or higher, g++ V.6 or higher, groff, libmysqlclient-dev(el), libtiff-dev(el)
.LP
\fI\fB²DPROG²:\fR
.br
acl, boost, boost-devel, boost-locale, cron, mariadb-server, p7zip
.br
Firebird (SuperServer, 32-bit) is currently not installed automatically and must be set up manually (see comments in the source file \fBimpgl.cpp\fR).
.SH IMPLICATIONS
The program has to take the following measures for its neat function:
.LP
\fB1)\fR Sudo (is missing per default in debian) will be installed if needed.
.br
The current linux user, if not already contained, will be entered into an administrator group mentioned in /etc/sudoers.
.LP
\fB2)\fR 'GNU make' will be installed if not present, automatically by calling 'sh install.sh'.
.LP
\fB3)\fR Creation of a logfile, per default \fB/var/log/²DPROG².log\fR.
.LP
\fB4)\fR Creation and adjustment of the configuration file \fB²DPROG².conf\fR in the program directory (default: \fB/usr/local/sbin/\fR).
.LP
\fB5)\fR Insertion of a line for the periodic automatic program call in root's crontab (if configured).
.LP
\fB6)\fR Creation of the configured database and the table \fBglalle\fR in MariaDB, if necessary; if necessary insertion of a MariaDB user.
.LP
\fB7)\fR Creation and use of the directory \fB/opt/firebird/gl\fR as well as intermediate and backup files in the source directory of the Gelbe Liste data sets.
.SH UNINSTALLING
Change in a terminal to the installation directory (for the same installed user, it's \fBcd ~/²DPROG²\fR, otherwise it will be displayed by \fB²DPROG² -info\fR).
.br
Call \fBmake uninstall\fR.
.br
Then the installed \fB²DPROG²\fR will be deleted and the script \fBuninstallinv\fR will be executed in reverse order which has been generated during the installation and execution of ²DPROG².
.br
Thereby additionally installed program packets and permissions are deleted.
.br
Configuration files, accumulated data (including the Firebird installation) and system relevant programs will not be deleted.
.br
Error messages originate mostly in efforts to delete a program already missing and can then be ignored.
.SH RETURN CODES
\fB0\fR: Normal return code
.br
\fB7\fR: The info screen (\fB²DPROG² -info\fR) has been displayed
.br
\fB8\fR: The help has been displayed
.br
\fB10\fR: Initializing of the database failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB11\fR: Checking of the database table failed and the program was stopped therefore
.br
\fB98\fR: Program stopped because it is already running once
.br
\fB113\fR: An sql command for the mariadb database failed with a miscellaneous error
.br
\fB115\fR: A database entry failed because of a full disk
.br
After calling \fB²DPROG² -vi\fR or \fB²DPROG² -vs\fR the return code of \fBvi\fR/\fBvim\fR will be passed
